        -:  234://! This assigns a shared pointer, but ONLY assigns if "target" is not equal to "source"
        -:  235://! If this is often the case, this manner of assignment is significantly faster (~20X faster)
        -:  236://! Since it avoids the need of an atomic incref/decref at the cost of a single pointer comparison
        -:  237://! Benchmark: https://gist.github.com/Mytherin/4db3faa8e233c4a9b874b21f62bb4b96
        -:  238://! If the shared pointers are not the same, the penalty is very low (on the order of 1%~ slower)
        -:  239://! This method should always be preferred if there is a (reasonable) chance that the pointers are the same
        -:  240:template<class T>
        -:  241:void AssignSharedPointer(shared_ptr<T> &target, const shared_ptr<T> &source) {
        -:  242:	if (target.get() != source.get()) {
        -:  243:		target = source;
        -:  244:	}
        -:  245:}
        -:  246:
